articles.description: Pressure is building on the Labor government over its stance on Gaza, with Labor minister Anne Aly confronted by pro-Palestinian activists who attended a constituent meeting on the weekend and new polling showing the extent of community anger.

articles.title: 'This death was preventable': Coroner examines death of mental health patient at Darwin hospital
articles.description: Nurses at Royal Darwin Hospital's secure mental health facility conducted observations of a schizophrenic patient via CCTV instead of physically checking on her for nine hours before she was found unresponsive, the NT coroner has heard.
articles.content:
